<h1><center>Anahita Apoorva</h1></u></font></center>
<hr color="maroon" size=5><font size=4 align="justify">
<p>Vocalists Anahita and Apoorva are among the most promising youngsters now in the Carnatic music field. The sisters had their initial musical inputs from their paternal grandmother, Shanthi Jayaraman.
<br>
<p>Siblings with immense talent and potential, the sisters have been making a name for themselves for several years now both in the Carnatic Music concerts and the contests scene.
<p>Their music is a product of very good training under their paternal grandmother, Smt.  Shanthi Jayaraman and presently under the tutelage of globally acclaimed musician-composer-director Chitravina Shri N Ravikiran.
 <br><center><img src="/static/images/aa1.jpg" height=300 width=300><br><br></center>
<p>Anahita Ravindran gave her maiden concert at the age of 9 in Raga Sudha Hall, Chennai. She has won several First prizes as also Tanpura Prizes and was adjudged Miss Voice by Carnatica which was judged by many eminent musical personalities. Naad Bhed, a classical music show conducted by SPIC MACAY and Doordarshan, saw her bag a place among the top 3 in the country in Carnatic Music. She was the 'Best On stage Performer' in Jaya TV’s Carnatic Music Idol, a finalist in RAJ TV’s Ragam Sangeetam, and has given several programs in various TV and FM Channels.
<p>She was awarded the ‘Best Performer’ by Krishna Gana Sabha for 2 consecutive years. <br>She is among the first winners of the  Excellence Award for Young Artistes from the Arts Culture India Foundation, and is also a recipient of the first prize in Padam singing conducted by The Music Academy. Having won the first prize in All India Radio, she has been graded as a B High Grade artist. She has also been the lead Vocalist for Dr. Vyjayantimala Bali’s Dance programs. (Complete list of awards won by Anahita)
​<br>
<p>Apoorva Ravindran gave her maiden concert when she was only 8. Also being awarded the first place in All India Radio and graded as a B grade artiste, she has won Tanpura prize from Mylapore Fine Arts and Super Singer award on Dikshitar Krithis conducted by Muttuswamy Dikshitar Trust. She participated in Tanishq Swarna Sangeetham by Raj TV and was adjudged the runner up after rigorous rounds of selection on various parameters. (Complete list of awards won by Apoorva)
<br>
</p>
